Package: councildown
Title: Brand Guideline Styling for New York City Council Reports & Dashboards
Version: 0.0.3.9000
Authors@R: person("Data", "Team", 
    email = "datainfo@council.nyc.gov", 
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package facilitates the creation of reports & dashboards for the
    New York City Council's data scientists. It also includes various useful
    functions for visually styling plots made with ggplot2 and maps made with
    leaflet.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: bookdown,
    ggplot2,
    leaflet,
    sf,
    htmltools,
    htmlwidgets,
    magrittr,
    knitr,
    dplyr (>= 0.8),
    mapview,
    leaflet.extras
Suggests: here,
    extrafont,
    sf
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
URL: https://newyorkcitycouncil.github.io/councildown/
